    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="witness" subtype="poem" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" rhyme="aa">
                <head type="title">L<hi rend="smallcaps">INES</hi> W<hi rend="smallcaps">RITTEN AT THE</hi> L<hi rend="smallcaps">AKES IN</hi> <placeName corresp="#CUMBERLAND">C<hi rend="smallcaps">UMBERLAND</hi></placeName>. <geogName corresp="#DERWENTWATER">D<hi rend="smallcaps">erwentwater</hi>.</geogName>.</head>
                <lg type="stanza">
                    <l>Sweet <geogName corresp="#DERWENTWATER">Derwent</geogName>! on thy winding shore,</l>
                    <l>Beside thy mountain forests hoar,</l>
                    <l>There would I love<ref type="gloss_textual" target="on_skiddaw_and_derwentwater_glosses_textual.php#LOVEGLOSS"/> to wander still;</l>
                    <l>And drink from out the rippling rill,</l>
                    <l>Which from thy rocky head doth fall,<ref type="gloss_textual" target="on_skiddaw_and_derwentwater_glosses_textual.php#DOTHFALLGLOSS"/></l>
                    <l>And mingles with the eagle&#x02BC;s call;</l>
                    <l>While from <geogName corresp="#HELVELLYN">Helvellyn</geogName> thunders break,<ref type="gloss_textual" target="on_skiddaw_and_derwentwater_glosses_textual.php#BREAKGLOSS"/></l>
                    <l>Re&#x2010;echoed from old <geogName corresp="#DERWENTWATER">Derwent</geogName>&#x02BC;s lake.<ref type="gloss_textual" target="on_skiddaw_and_derwentwater_glosses_textual.php#FROMOLDGLOSS"/></l>
                    <l>And where the lightning&#x02BC;s flaming dart</l>
                    <l>Plays o&#x02BC;er the Poet&#x02BC;s eye, and warms his heart:</l>
                    <l>Though such thy glories, Earth, thy proudest whole,</l>
                    <l>Can never satiate the grasping soul!<ref type="gloss_textual" target="on_skiddaw_and_derwentwater_glosses_textual.php#DARTGLOSS"/></l>
                </lg>
            </div>
